**No centralized middleware enforces scope**. Instead, each handler:
1. Accepts `workspaceId` (URL param or request body)
2. Calls `resolveWorkspaceRecord(surreal, workspaceId)` to verify workspace exists
3. Throws `HttpError(404, "workspace not found")` if missing

**File**: `/Users/marcus/conductor/workspaces/brain/riga/app/src/server/workspace/workspace-scope.ts`

Example from `workspace-routes.ts` (line 178):
```typescript
const workspaceRecord = await resolveWorkspaceRecord(deps.surreal, workspaceId);
const workspace = await deps.surreal.select<WorkspaceRow>(workspaceRecord);
if (!workspace) {
  throw new HttpError(404, `workspace not found: ${workspaceId}`);
}
```

